President Cyril Ramaphosa will announce the new National Commissioner of Police in an address to the nation on Thursday. #eNCA #DStv403 Editor's note: This event will be broadcast live on eNCA.com and DStv Now and is expected to start soon. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will announce the new National Commissioner of Police in an address to the nation on Thursday. READ: Khehla Sitole | Processes had to be followed - Ramaphosa "The President’s appointment of a new National Commissioner will ensure continuity in the most senior position in the South African Police Service following the departure from office today of National Commissioner Khehla Sitole," a statement released by the Presidency read. Thursday was Sitole's last day in office and everyone is eager to know who will be his successor. Last month, the president announced the early termination of the national police commissioner's contract, saying it's in the best interests of the country.